    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Students of all the departments of a college who have successfully completed the registration process are eligible to vote in the upcoming college elections. However, by the time the due date for registration was over, it was found that surprisingly none of the students from the Department of Human Sciences had completed the registration process.</p>\n<p>Based only on the information provided above, which one of the following sets of statements can be logically inferred with certainty?</p>\n<p>(i) All those students who would not be eligible to vote in the college elections would certainly belong to the Department of Human Sciences.</p>\n<p>(ii) None of the students from departments other than Human Sciences failed to complete the registration process within the due time.</p>\n<p>(iii) All the eligible voters would certainly be students who are not from the Department of Human Sciences.</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "(i) and (ii)"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "(i) and (iii)"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "only (i)"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "only (iii)"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Based on the information provided, only statement (iii) can be logically inferred with certainty: All the eligible voters would certainly be students who are not from the Department of Human Sciences.</p>\n\n<p>We know that students from all departments who have successfully completed the registration process are eligible to vote, but none of the students from the Department of Human Sciences completed the registration process. Therefore, it can be inferred that none of the students from that department are eligible to vote, and that all eligible voters are students from departments other than Human Sciences.</p>\n\n<p>Statements (i) and (ii) cannot be inferred from the information given. We cannot say that all those who are not eligible to vote would belong to the Department of Human Sciences (statement i), nor can we say that all students from departments other than Human Sciences completed the registration process (statement ii).</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "gate-ee-2023",
    "difficulty": null
  },
